50|$|<b>The</b> <b>ember</b> days {{began on}} the Wednesday {{immediately}} following those days. This meant, for instance, that if September 14 were a Tuesday, <b>the</b> <b>ember</b> days would occur on September 15, 17, and 18. As a result, <b>the</b> <b>ember</b> days in September could fall after either {{the second or third}} Sunday in September. This, however, was always the liturgical Third Week of September, since the First Sunday of September was the Sunday closest to September 1 (August 29 to September 4). As a simplification of the liturgical calendar, Pope John XXIII modified this so that the Third Sunday was the third Sunday actually within the calendar month. Thus if September 14 were a Sunday, September 24, 26 and 27 would be <b>ember</b> days, <b>the</b> latest dates possible; with September 14 as a Saturday, however, <b>the</b> <b>ember</b> days would occur on September 18, 20 and 21 - the earliest possible dates.|$|R
