2500|$|The drill {{offers an}} ancient method of {{starting}} fire without matches or a lighter, {{a method that}} applies friction to generate heat. The heat eventually produces an <b>ember</b> in <b>the</b> burnt sawdust. <b>The</b> <b>ember</b> is tiny, smaller than {{the head of a}} cigarette, and fragile. Once <b>the</b> <b>ember</b> is formed it is carefully placed into a [...] "tinder bundle" [...] (a bird's type nest of stringy, fluffy, and combustible material). Once <b>the</b> <b>ember</b> is in <b>the</b> tinder bundle it is then carefully nurtured and coaxed into flame. Once the tinder bundle bursts into flame, it is placed into the fuel that has been assembled ready for ignition.|$|R
